1
00:00:34,492 --> 00:00:37,120
[Fisk] The painting that's intended
for this wall

2
00:00:37,954 --> 00:00:40,498
is something I am specially attached to.

3
00:00:40,582 --> 00:00:43,668
[Lee] Of course. <i>Rabbit in a Snowstorm.</i>

4
00:00:43,752 --> 00:00:45,587
Yes, the agreement.

5
00:00:46,546 --> 00:00:51,051
It said I was to get
all my belongings restored to me.

6
00:00:51,134 --> 00:00:55,764
Precisely. And we might be able
to use this violation of terms

7
00:00:55,847 --> 00:00:57,682
to lobby the feds for something else.

8
00:00:57,766 --> 00:00:59,100
The painting!

9
00:01:02,645 --> 00:01:04,522
That's what I'm interested in.

10
00:01:05,231 --> 00:01:09,611
I can assure you we're doing
everything in our power, but...

11
00:01:09,694 --> 00:01:12,572
there's a challenge
to your ownership claim.

12
00:01:25,418 --> 00:01:26,836
It comes home.

13
00:01:27,796 --> 00:01:29,089
Do you understand?

14
00:01:46,147 --> 00:01:47,941
Lawyer's out! Cameras back on!

15
00:01:56,741 --> 00:01:59,244
[agent over radio]<i> Wellers,</i>
<i>we have a situation. Report to the CP.</i>

16
00:02:00,328 --> 00:02:01,412
[Wellers] Shit.

17
00:02:03,998 --> 00:02:05,750
Inside. Shut the door.

18
00:04:23,054 --> 00:04:24,514
[Fisk] Show them to me.

19
00:04:28,268 --> 00:04:29,560
[typing]

20
00:04:30,520 --> 00:04:32,605
[woman over radio] <i>All units</i>
<i>on the citywide, NYPD...</i>

21
00:04:32,689 --> 00:04:34,440
[radio chatter continues indistinctly]

22
00:04:36,109 --> 00:04:39,612
[Doyle] <i>Shit. Are you hearing this?</i>
<i>What happened at the </i>Bulletin?

23
00:04:39,696 --> 00:04:43,241
<i>We should be there,</i>
<i>not stuck here with this asshole.</i>

24
00:04:43,324 --> 00:04:44,409
<i>He go to bed?</i>

25
00:04:44,492 --> 00:04:48,037
[Doyle] <i>Turned in early.</i>
<i>Nice and cozy, while the world explodes.</i>

26
00:04:48,121 --> 00:04:50,623
And now the news, Mrs. Shelby.

27
00:04:52,041 --> 00:04:55,169
<i>...rushed to nearby hospitals</i>
<i>in critical condition.</i>

28
00:04:55,253 --> 00:04:59,090
<i>But what we do know is that,</i>
<i>according to several eyewitnesses,</i>

29
00:04:59,173 --> 00:05:01,592
<i>the brutal attack on the </i>Bulletin<i> staff</i>

30
00:05:01,676 --> 00:05:05,054
<i>has been carried out</i>
<i>by none other than Daredevil.</i>

31
00:05:05,638 --> 00:05:08,599
<i>The word from the witnesses</i>
<i>we've spoken with is that Daredevil,</i>

32
00:05:08,683 --> 00:05:11,394
<i>Hell's Kitchen's renowned vigilante,</i>
<i>is the perpetrator.</i>

33
00:05:11,477 --> 00:05:14,147
<i>...they don't know the whereabouts</i>
<i>of Daredevil or whether...</i>

34
00:05:14,230 --> 00:05:19,402
<i>This brutal act hits Hell's Kitchen after</i>
<i>a period of relative calm in the city,</i>

35
00:05:19,485 --> 00:05:22,030
<i>with the FBI arresting</i>
<i>many of New York's...</i>

36
00:05:26,576 --> 00:05:28,578
[theme music playing]

37
00:06:33,309 --> 00:06:36,104
You're missing the point. He didn't
just find someone to wear my suit.

38
00:06:36,187 --> 00:06:39,440
Someone as fast and skilled as I've
ever seen, and I couldn't take him.

39
00:06:39,524 --> 00:06:41,901
-He found someone to kill me.
-Matthew...

40
00:06:41,984 --> 00:06:44,529
I was stupid enough to think
that I had Fisk cornered.

41
00:06:44,612 --> 00:06:48,199
He knew I'd find the witness,
and I just brought the sheep to slaughter.

42
00:06:48,282 --> 00:06:49,534
Jasper Evans is dead.

43
00:06:49,617 --> 00:06:52,286
He's dead and he leaves a son behind,
and that's on me!

44
00:06:53,037 --> 00:06:56,666
I was so sure that I finally
was out in front of this bastard.

45
00:06:56,749 --> 00:06:58,251
And Fisk, he knew I thought that.

46
00:06:58,334 --> 00:06:59,710
-He was waiting for me.
-Matthew--

47
00:06:59,794 --> 00:07:01,629
Foggy and Karen both could've been killed.

48
00:07:01,712 --> 00:07:05,508
And there would have been nothing
I could have done to stop it. Nothing.

49
00:07:05,591 --> 00:07:08,636
You're losing blood.
I need to stitch you up.

50
00:07:08,719 --> 00:07:12,348
I listened to you.
I listened to you, and they almost died.

51
00:07:13,975 --> 00:07:16,227
God damn it. I'm such an idiot.

52
00:07:18,187 --> 00:07:19,188
No.

53
00:07:21,649 --> 00:07:22,984
I'm the idiot.

54
00:07:23,860 --> 00:07:28,030
I told you to involve your friends,
and I made things worse.

55
00:07:31,993 --> 00:07:36,372
I'm used to putting on a brave face when
people bring their troubles to the church.

56
00:07:37,540 --> 00:07:40,376
And I find that they
don't just bring their troubles,

57
00:07:40,460 --> 00:07:43,880
they bring their answers, too,
if you let them talk enough.

58
00:07:44,714 --> 00:07:45,756
But...

59
00:07:46,883 --> 00:07:52,472
what you're dealing with
is so far beyond my experience that...

60
00:07:56,350 --> 00:07:57,518
Well...

61
00:07:58,561 --> 00:08:03,483
all I can hope to do is help keep
your wounds stitched and your head clear,

62
00:08:03,566 --> 00:08:05,443
so you can be safe.

63
00:08:07,570 --> 00:08:10,823
And I'll be more careful
about giving advice to the Devil.

64
00:08:12,158 --> 00:08:17,413
And, occasionally, possibly,
I'll try to keep my mouth shut.

65
00:08:17,497 --> 00:08:19,165
Could I get that in writing?

66
00:08:22,001 --> 00:08:24,128
Look, I know you were just trying to help.

67
00:08:25,254 --> 00:08:27,840
Now, can I please see to those wounds?

68
00:08:40,186 --> 00:08:41,562
[exhales]

69
00:08:53,908 --> 00:08:55,493
Can I ask you something?

70
00:08:56,077 --> 00:08:57,119
Yeah.

71
00:08:57,495 --> 00:08:59,747
[breathes heavily]

72
00:08:59,830 --> 00:09:04,752
What if you stopped this fight,
took time to heal...

73
00:09:05,294 --> 00:09:08,256
and let other people like you
go after Fisk?

74
00:09:11,467 --> 00:09:13,010
This isn't their fight.

75
00:09:14,720 --> 00:09:16,389
Fisk is my problem.

76
00:09:22,144 --> 00:09:23,729
-Sorry.
-It's okay.

77
00:09:26,190 --> 00:09:30,403
The problem is,
he's always five steps ahead of me.

78
00:09:32,446 --> 00:09:34,282
I don't know if I can beat him.

79
00:09:36,200 --> 00:09:39,328
And I don't know if I can beat
the man he sent to kill me.

80
00:09:40,496 --> 00:09:43,708
You won't know for certain
till you find him.

81
00:09:46,669 --> 00:09:49,171
I thought you were gonna keep
your thoughts to yourself.

82
00:09:50,423 --> 00:09:53,342
-You really want me to do that?
-[chuckles softly] No.

83
00:09:57,305 --> 00:10:00,433
If he was wearing
a copy of your Devil suit...

84
00:10:00,516 --> 00:10:02,810
Well, he didn't get it at Sears.

85
00:10:04,270 --> 00:10:05,771
How good a copy was it?

86
00:10:11,235 --> 00:10:12,695
It was perfect.

87
00:10:15,448 --> 00:10:17,408
-[Karen panting on TV]
-[gunshot on TV]

88
00:10:22,538 --> 00:10:25,249
[Dex] <i>Hello, Karen.</i>
<i>It's nice to see you again.</i>

89
00:10:30,004 --> 00:10:32,882
Was there anyone else
in the room named Karen?

90
00:10:33,507 --> 00:10:35,635
Or on the whole <i>Bulletin</i> staff?

91
00:10:35,718 --> 00:10:38,262
I'm advising my client
not to answer any questions

92
00:10:38,346 --> 00:10:39,972
that treat her like an asshole.

93
00:10:40,723 --> 00:10:44,060
[Ray] There was not.
He was talking to you.

94
00:10:47,521 --> 00:10:49,565
-Why don't we watch it again? See--
-No.

95
00:10:50,483 --> 00:10:53,819
-He was talking to me. That's true.
-[Ray] Okay.

96
00:10:54,403 --> 00:10:56,530
-Good.
-[Karen] But I've never met him before.

97
00:10:58,699 --> 00:11:03,704
Well, according to your own newspaper,
you've met Daredevil at least twice.

98
00:11:03,788 --> 00:11:05,289
That psycho's not Daredevil.

99
00:11:05,373 --> 00:11:07,166
I got a pretty good look at him, too.

100
00:11:07,750 --> 00:11:08,834
Could have fooled me.

101
00:11:08,918 --> 00:11:13,631
Do you think every fat guy with
a white beard and red suit is Santa Claus?

102
00:11:13,714 --> 00:11:16,425
If he comes down my chimney
and leaves presents under the tree.

103
00:11:16,509 --> 00:11:19,762
Exactly. If he acted like Santa.
This guy doesn't act like Daredevil.

104
00:11:19,845 --> 00:11:21,430
Based on your two encounters?

105
00:11:22,890 --> 00:11:24,100
Dig a little deeper.

106
00:11:24,642 --> 00:11:26,352
Why don't you read everything?

107
00:11:26,977 --> 00:11:29,772
He doesn't kill people, ever.
It's not Daredevil.

108
00:11:29,855 --> 00:11:31,440
So you keep saying.

109
00:11:31,524 --> 00:11:34,568
Did you ever look into Felix Manning?
Red Lion Bank?

110
00:11:34,652 --> 00:11:36,696
Any of the leads
that I dropped in your lap?

111
00:11:38,322 --> 00:11:39,699
They're on my to-do list.

112
00:11:41,075 --> 00:11:42,326
This is bullshit.

113
00:11:44,787 --> 00:11:46,747
He dropped your name, Ms. Page.

114
00:11:46,831 --> 00:11:49,083
Used your gun to murder someone.

115
00:11:49,166 --> 00:11:50,584
And in this entire shitshow,

116
00:11:50,668 --> 00:11:53,421
you're the one person
he didn't lay a finger on.

117
00:11:53,504 --> 00:11:56,674
So I'm sorry that you think
that this is bullshit,

118
00:11:56,757 --> 00:11:58,467
but something doesn't add up.

119
00:11:58,551 --> 00:12:00,803
So we're gonna keep
going over this until it does.

120
00:12:00,886 --> 00:12:04,014
It's not gonna add up until you start
asking the right questions.

121
00:12:04,098 --> 00:12:05,975
How about this one? Where's Matt Murdock?

122
00:12:06,684 --> 00:12:09,895
Yet another fine example of a question
that's besides the friggin' point!

123
00:12:09,979 --> 00:12:11,772
You were supposed to deliver him,
Mr. Nelson.

124
00:12:11,856 --> 00:12:14,024
But there are zero Matt Murdocks
in my custody.

125
00:12:14,108 --> 00:12:16,360
Zero Jasper Evans left alive.

126
00:12:18,028 --> 00:12:22,199
Think that's random?
He kills the one guy with dirt on Fisk.

127
00:12:22,283 --> 00:12:24,869
You know that already?
Is that why you don't wanna go there?

128
00:12:24,952 --> 00:12:25,953
-Karen--
-What?

129
00:12:31,792 --> 00:12:35,755
That psycho in a suit
did Agent Nadeem a huge favor.

130
00:12:37,298 --> 00:12:41,552
Now there's no one left to tell the world
what a fool Fisk is making of the FBI.

131
00:12:44,013 --> 00:12:46,932
Did you know Daredevil
was gonna attack the <i>Bulletin?</i>

132
00:12:47,016 --> 00:12:48,684
Is that why you brought
your gun last night?

133
00:12:48,768 --> 00:12:50,561
Okay. We're done here.

134
00:12:59,278 --> 00:13:00,321
[door opens]

135
00:13:00,988 --> 00:13:01,822
[door closes]

136
00:13:05,034 --> 00:13:06,202
Are you okay?

137
00:13:07,244 --> 00:13:10,372
No, I'm definitely not okay.

138
00:13:10,456 --> 00:13:12,249
[cell phone ringing]

139
00:13:13,834 --> 00:13:16,045
[cell phones ringing and chiming]

140
00:13:17,588 --> 00:13:20,424
None of the people who own those phones
are okay, either.

141
00:13:20,966 --> 00:13:22,551
-Come on. Let's go.
-No...

142
00:13:23,552 --> 00:13:27,765
I don't get it. You... You almost died.
That doesn't leave a mark?

143
00:13:28,349 --> 00:13:30,351
I don't have time to think about that.

144
00:13:30,434 --> 00:13:33,395
Right now,
Agent Nadeem's got all my attention.

145
00:13:33,479 --> 00:13:37,274
If he digs into Jasper Evans, he'll know
we're telling the truth about Fisk.

146
00:13:37,358 --> 00:13:39,693
Then he'll dig into the rest of it.
I hope.

147
00:13:54,291 --> 00:13:55,459
I did this.

148
00:13:55,543 --> 00:13:57,586
[Foggy] Wilson Fisk did this.

149
00:14:00,256 --> 00:14:03,008
Evans wouldn't have come to the <i>Bulletin</i>
if I hadn't threatened his son.

150
00:14:03,592 --> 00:14:05,052
This isn't on you.

151
00:14:05,135 --> 00:14:07,346
And this isn't the time
to give up the fight.

152
00:14:07,429 --> 00:14:10,474
-We need to find Matt--
- No. Um...

153
00:14:11,267 --> 00:14:13,310
-I'm gonna go to the hospital.
-[cell phone vibrating]

154
00:14:13,394 --> 00:14:14,436
Are you hurt?

155
00:14:15,896 --> 00:14:17,398
I'm the only one who wasn't.

156
00:14:19,984 --> 00:14:22,444
Marci. I should take this. She's worried.

157
00:14:31,370 --> 00:14:32,371
Hey, babe.

158
00:14:33,163 --> 00:14:34,748
Yeah, I'm okay. I'm fine.

159
00:14:36,500 --> 00:14:39,628
I know. I'm sorry, it's just been crazy.
The time has--

160
00:14:40,504 --> 00:14:41,964
Seema, I'm fine.

161
00:14:42,965 --> 00:14:43,966
Really, I--

162
00:14:47,386 --> 00:14:49,013
Seems, I wasn't even there.

163
00:14:50,222 --> 00:14:52,474
I got there after it was all over.

164
00:14:53,434 --> 00:14:54,518
That's right.

165
00:14:57,646 --> 00:14:59,356
I'll be home tonight, okay?

166
00:15:00,190 --> 00:15:01,233
[knock at door]

167
00:15:02,610 --> 00:15:04,194
Oh, shit. That's tonight?

168
00:15:06,864 --> 00:15:10,075
No. No, no. Don't cancel. Um...

169
00:15:11,410 --> 00:15:13,120
It'll be good to see the family.

170
00:15:13,203 --> 00:15:15,372
And good for Sami, you know?

171
00:15:15,456 --> 00:15:19,043
And let him know
everything really is all right.

172
00:15:23,005 --> 00:15:24,465
I love you, too.

173
00:15:28,802 --> 00:15:30,220
Where is he?

174
00:15:31,221 --> 00:15:34,141
-[Betsy] Damn, it's cold out here.
-[Melvin] You got your hat?

175
00:15:34,224 --> 00:15:35,309
I could get your hat.

176
00:15:35,392 --> 00:15:37,728
[Betsy] No, Melvin, it's okay.
I'm in the office today.

177
00:15:37,811 --> 00:15:38,812
[Melvin] Okay.

178
00:15:50,407 --> 00:15:51,909
I made you cheese and pickles.

179
00:15:52,868 --> 00:15:53,953
Thanks, love.

180
00:15:56,121 --> 00:15:59,083
-[Melvin] You got your gun?
-[Betsy] Of course. Right here.

181
00:15:59,166 --> 00:16:00,167
What's going on?

182
00:16:00,250 --> 00:16:02,211
You've been acting strange all morning.

183
00:16:02,294 --> 00:16:03,128
[Melvin] I...

184
00:16:03,671 --> 00:16:05,047
worry about you.

185
00:16:05,589 --> 00:16:07,508
Because I hang out
with paroled cons like you?

186
00:16:07,591 --> 00:16:09,218
[Melvin] 'Cause they're not like me. [Betsy] I can take care of myself,
big man.

187
00:16:11,762 --> 00:16:15,099
You be good today.
I'll make asopao for dinner.

188
00:16:15,182 --> 00:16:16,225
[Melvin] Okay.

189
00:16:18,727 --> 00:16:19,728
Love you.

190
00:16:29,321 --> 00:16:31,281
[Matt] Betsy's your parole officer.

191
00:16:35,160 --> 00:16:38,539
Please don't tell anyone.
It's against the rules.

192
00:16:38,622 --> 00:16:41,125
I don't care
what you do with Betsy, Melvin.

193
00:16:42,167 --> 00:16:43,419
You know why I'm here.

194
00:16:44,753 --> 00:16:46,463
Fisk made me make the suit.

195
00:16:48,132 --> 00:16:49,258
Did that man hurt you?

196
00:16:50,134 --> 00:16:51,301
I'm sorry.

197
00:16:51,385 --> 00:16:52,511
Who was he?

198
00:16:53,053 --> 00:16:54,221
He didn't tell me his name.

199
00:16:54,304 --> 00:16:57,516
But I can make you a new one...
to protect you against him.

200
00:16:57,599 --> 00:17:00,269
-It'd be a fair fight.
-I don't want the suit anymore.

201
00:17:00,811 --> 00:17:02,146
You don't like it?

202
00:17:02,229 --> 00:17:03,939
I've outgrown what it stood for.

203
00:17:06,108 --> 00:17:09,737
When you made my suit,
there were molds, measurements.

204
00:17:12,740 --> 00:17:14,575
At the workshop, maybe there's something.

205
00:17:14,658 --> 00:17:17,161
I've been to the workshop.
It's been burned down.

206
00:17:17,244 --> 00:17:21,498
Yeah, I burned it down,
because I didn't want to help Fisk, but...

207
00:17:21,582 --> 00:17:23,834
he made me a new shop
and he threatened Betsy.

208
00:17:26,211 --> 00:17:30,632
People died
because you helped him, Melvin.

209
00:17:31,383 --> 00:17:34,344
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

210
00:17:37,514 --> 00:17:38,932
Where is your new shop?

211
00:18:21,350 --> 00:18:22,518
[Marci] Foggy Bear?

212
00:18:25,854 --> 00:18:28,816
Oh, my God! Are you all right?

213
00:18:28,899 --> 00:18:30,651
When did you get here?

214
00:18:30,734 --> 00:18:33,737
I tried to stay awake.
I've been watching the news all night.

215
00:18:33,821 --> 00:18:35,197
Are you hurt?

216
00:18:36,657 --> 00:18:38,283
Babe, talk to me.

217
00:18:40,494 --> 00:18:41,703
I'm okay.

218
00:18:42,746 --> 00:18:44,039
I'm just tired.

219
00:18:52,089 --> 00:18:53,590
Let's get you to bed.

220
00:18:58,595 --> 00:18:59,596
Babe?

221
00:19:21,952 --> 00:19:23,120
[Ray] Jasper Evans.

222
00:19:24,037 --> 00:19:26,498
Locked up in '91
on a couple of murder two counts.

223
00:19:27,082 --> 00:19:30,544
Seems he walked into a convenience store,
got talked to the wrong way,

224
00:19:30,627 --> 00:19:32,212
ended up shooting an honest cashier

225
00:19:32,296 --> 00:19:35,382
and a sweet old granny
picking up her Sunday Powerball ticket.

226
00:19:37,134 --> 00:19:38,969
-Yeah.
-Yeah?

227
00:19:39,052 --> 00:19:41,847
Warden, this lifer
was supposed to be serving

228
00:19:41,930 --> 00:19:44,224
a year in the hole
for shanking Wilson Fisk.

229
00:19:44,766 --> 00:19:45,726
Is that a question?

230
00:19:45,809 --> 00:19:49,855
How could he be in the hole and get killed
in a newspaper office at the same time?

231
00:19:49,938 --> 00:19:53,901
Some pencil-pusher must've checked
the wrong box and let him out by mistake.

232
00:19:57,070 --> 00:20:00,115
Look. I'm not trying to jam you up.

233
00:20:01,158 --> 00:20:03,577
I'm just trying to nail down
how he got out.

234
00:20:04,620 --> 00:20:06,496
And who might have wanted him dead.

235
00:20:08,248 --> 00:20:10,125
I need answers, Warden.

236
00:20:12,294 --> 00:20:14,796
You got nothing? Seriously?

237
00:20:19,009 --> 00:20:20,302
I want my lawyer.

238
00:20:26,850 --> 00:20:28,977
I talked to the <i>Bulletin</i> reporter.

239
00:20:29,061 --> 00:20:32,231
Jasper Evans was going to say
that Fisk staged his own shanking.

240
00:20:32,314 --> 00:20:34,066
He had him released
from prison as payback.

241
00:20:34,149 --> 00:20:35,150
Jesus.

242
00:20:36,360 --> 00:20:38,153
Tell me the warden disputes that.

243
00:20:38,237 --> 00:20:40,489
He's more concerned
with covering his own ass.

244
00:20:40,572 --> 00:20:43,158
-He's lawyered up.
-Oh, shit.

245
00:20:44,868 --> 00:20:48,121
It's all hearsay.
I mean, Evans might have been lying.

246
00:20:48,205 --> 00:20:49,957
And maybe he was telling the truth. We gotta kick this up the chain.

247
00:20:52,376 --> 00:20:53,961
-Who are you calling?
-The ADIC.

248
00:20:55,087 --> 00:20:58,173
And tell him what?
We don't know all the facts.

249
00:20:58,257 --> 00:21:01,510
Except there's a damn good chance
that Fisk is manipulating us.

250
00:21:09,643 --> 00:21:11,395
If it's true,

251
00:21:11,478 --> 00:21:15,565
every asshole we put away with Fisk's help
will be back on the street by morning.

252
00:21:16,733 --> 00:21:20,195
Everything we've done,
the people we've lost,

253
00:21:20,279 --> 00:21:21,822
it will all be for nothing.

254
00:21:22,406 --> 00:21:24,157
You can't unring that bell.

255
00:21:24,241 --> 00:21:26,368
Just give me a chance
to figure out if it's true.

256
00:21:26,451 --> 00:21:27,577
How?

257
00:21:28,954 --> 00:21:30,289
I need two days.

258
00:21:31,164 --> 00:21:32,708
You want a pony, too?

259
00:21:32,791 --> 00:21:35,335
Just let me get the facts.

260
00:21:35,919 --> 00:21:38,046
If Fisk really did play us, we'll bury that son of a bitch together.

261
00:21:47,806 --> 00:21:48,682
Wow.

262
00:21:50,809 --> 00:21:52,144
I don't know what got into me.

263
00:21:52,227 --> 00:21:53,312
It's okay.

264
00:21:54,354 --> 00:21:56,773
I mean, it was way, way better than okay.

265
00:21:56,857 --> 00:21:59,109
Like, way better.

266
00:21:59,192 --> 00:22:02,362
[chuckles] I mean, I get it.

267
00:22:03,613 --> 00:22:05,574
After what you went through last night.

268
00:22:08,035 --> 00:22:10,203
I was convinced I was gonna die.

269
00:22:10,287 --> 00:22:13,707
The last thing I remember thinking was,
"Not yet."

270
00:22:13,790 --> 00:22:15,876
Oh, you must've been so scared.

271
00:22:15,959 --> 00:22:18,754
More than I've ever been
in my entire life.

272
00:22:19,338 --> 00:22:24,926
But there was something else beneath it.
This feeling of being unsettled.

273
00:22:25,719 --> 00:22:28,930
[stammers] Important things left undone.

274
00:22:32,434 --> 00:22:33,435
Marry me.

275
00:22:35,312 --> 00:22:37,064
-Stop.
-I'm serious.

276
00:22:37,147 --> 00:22:40,650
-Let's go to the courthouse right now.
-Foggy Bear, slow down.

277
00:22:40,734 --> 00:22:43,236
I love you, Marci, and I'm pretty sure
that you love me, too.

278
00:22:43,320 --> 00:22:44,821
I do love you.

279
00:22:45,739 --> 00:22:49,534
But when you propose,
I want it to be from your heart.

280
00:22:49,618 --> 00:22:51,203
Not from this.

281
00:22:54,956 --> 00:22:55,957
[kisses] Shit.

282
00:23:02,631 --> 00:23:04,674
I'm gonna be late for my deposition.

283
00:23:07,719 --> 00:23:11,181
Go. Shower. I'll pick this up.

284
00:23:41,044 --> 00:23:42,587
What the hell?

285
00:23:45,048 --> 00:23:47,759
[Ellison] Think about what Amber
would have wanted. You know?

286
00:23:50,720 --> 00:23:53,682
[Carla] They want to take her off
of life support.

287
00:23:54,266 --> 00:23:55,684
I'll let you know what we decide.

288
00:23:55,767 --> 00:23:57,227
[Ellison] Okay. I'm so sorry.

289
00:24:05,694 --> 00:24:06,695
I'm...

290
00:24:06,778 --> 00:24:08,822
[woman over PA]
<i>All surgical residents to pre-op.</i>

291
00:24:08,905 --> 00:24:10,907
<i>All surgical residents to pre-op.</i>

292
00:24:12,909 --> 00:24:16,246
<i>Chief ortho resident to ER.</i>
<i>Chief ortho resident to ER.</i>

293
00:24:16,329 --> 00:24:18,123
-[Ellison] Oh, hey.
-[Karen] Hey.

294
00:24:21,960 --> 00:24:23,253
How are you feeling?

295
00:24:23,336 --> 00:24:24,254
[clicks tongue]

296
00:24:25,505 --> 00:24:26,798
I'm full of Percocet.

297
00:24:27,757 --> 00:24:28,925
Jell-O.

298
00:24:30,093 --> 00:24:31,553
-Rage.
-[Karen chuckles]

299
00:24:33,305 --> 00:24:34,181
Uh...

300
00:24:34,723 --> 00:24:35,724
Amber?

301
00:24:35,807 --> 00:24:37,017
Oh, she's on...

302
00:24:39,144 --> 00:24:44,274
She's brain-dead.
Just, uh, machines keeping her alive.

303
00:24:45,609 --> 00:24:47,527
-It wasn't worth it.
-Karen...

304
00:24:47,611 --> 00:24:49,029
Look, three people died.

305
00:24:50,071 --> 00:24:51,615
Why? Because I had to pick a fight?

306
00:24:51,698 --> 00:24:54,284
I'm pretty sure
that's what we're supposed to do. Sometimes, we get our asses kicked.

307
00:24:57,746 --> 00:24:59,998
Could you get me the water?
It's over there.

308
00:25:00,749 --> 00:25:05,462
Don't think you have some proprietary
claim over sticking it to Fisk.

309
00:25:05,545 --> 00:25:09,216
You know, this fight belongs
to every person in Hell's Kitchen.

310
00:25:09,299 --> 00:25:13,595
And I'm one of them,
so I intend to keep fighting.

311
00:25:13,678 --> 00:25:17,849
We're gonna go to print today, tomorrow,
and the next day and the next day.

312
00:25:20,519 --> 00:25:26,024
Here. I want you to write down
everything you know about Daredevil.

313
00:25:26,107 --> 00:25:28,151
His connection to Fisk.

314
00:25:28,235 --> 00:25:31,696
The man who attacked us last night,
it wasn't Daredevil.

315
00:25:35,116 --> 00:25:36,409
Who was it, then?

316
00:25:36,493 --> 00:25:37,577
[exhales]

317
00:25:38,411 --> 00:25:39,913
I don't know.

318
00:25:42,040 --> 00:25:43,750
But you know it wasn't Daredevil.

319
00:25:48,588 --> 00:25:52,425
Karen, do you know who Daredevil is?

320
00:25:57,681 --> 00:26:00,183
Don't ask me that. Please.

321
00:26:00,267 --> 00:26:01,351
Why not?

322
00:26:04,145 --> 00:26:10,902
Karen, if you know something,
you've gotta tell me right now.

323
00:26:13,488 --> 00:26:15,824
[stammers] I can't.

324
00:26:16,825 --> 00:26:22,581
Some piece of shit attacked my people,
in my house!

325
00:26:25,584 --> 00:26:26,918
And if you know anything,

326
00:26:27,002 --> 00:26:30,714
anything that will get me closer
to finding out who he is,

327
00:26:30,797 --> 00:26:34,134
then, God damn it,
you are going to tell me!

328
00:26:36,344 --> 00:26:40,098
Or you can go clean out your desk.

329
00:27:05,373 --> 00:27:06,583
[keypad beeping]

330
00:27:06,666 --> 00:27:08,293
[gate buzzes]

331
00:27:33,401 --> 00:27:34,903
[Matt] Why is the suit here?

332
00:27:36,154 --> 00:27:39,658
[Melvin] That's not the one he wore.
Fisk made me make two.

333
00:27:39,741 --> 00:27:40,784
Why?

334
00:27:43,703 --> 00:27:45,914
-Ask him yourself.
-What are you doing?

335
00:27:47,165 --> 00:27:48,708
I have to go now. He said.

336
00:27:48,792 --> 00:27:50,418
-Don't do this.
-I don't have a choice.

337
00:27:50,502 --> 00:27:51,336
He'll come for Betsy.

338
00:27:51,419 --> 00:27:54,172
Why'd he ask you to trap me here?
Is he coming? Tell me who wore the suit!

339
00:27:54,255 --> 00:27:55,882
I will find him.
I will put an end to this.

340
00:27:55,965 --> 00:27:58,343
I can't. Fisk will know.
And he'll hurt Betsy.

341
00:27:58,426 --> 00:28:00,428
If you really loved her,
you'd cut her loose.

342
00:28:00,512 --> 00:28:03,098
This life doesn't work with Betsys.

343
00:28:03,181 --> 00:28:05,225
[grunting]

344
00:28:06,726 --> 00:28:08,228
[Melvin] I can't let you leave!

345
00:28:20,031 --> 00:28:22,534
[Matt groaning]

346
00:29:04,701 --> 00:29:07,495
-Someone's coming.
-I'm not supposed to be here.

347
00:29:20,800 --> 00:29:23,553
It's the FBI, Melvin.
Why would Fisk send...

348
00:29:24,679 --> 00:29:26,806
They're supposed to find you
with the suit.

349
00:29:30,560 --> 00:29:31,644
Oh, God.

350
00:29:31,728 --> 00:29:35,273
He's framing me for being Daredevil.
Oh, God.

351
00:29:36,900 --> 00:29:39,027
Melvin, come on, he's tricking you.

352
00:29:39,110 --> 00:29:41,446
Please. Betsy's all I have.

353
00:29:41,529 --> 00:29:44,574
Once Fisk has me, he will kill you both.

354
00:29:46,159 --> 00:29:49,454
-Oh, man.
-You gotta help me, or Betsy's dead.

355
00:29:49,537 --> 00:29:50,914
Who did you make the suit for?

356
00:29:50,997 --> 00:29:53,291
He never told me his name...

357
00:29:54,501 --> 00:29:55,919
but he was an FBI agent.

358
00:29:56,795 --> 00:29:58,171
How do you know that?

359
00:29:58,713 --> 00:30:01,633
He was talking about it
with the man who brought him.

360
00:30:01,716 --> 00:30:03,760
[agent 1] Breach. Breach. Breach.

361
00:30:05,929 --> 00:30:07,388
[agent 2] FBI! Don't move!

362
00:30:09,390 --> 00:30:10,517
Go! Go! Go!

363
00:30:51,599 --> 00:30:53,560
[agent 2] Stop fighting, or we'll shoot!

364
00:31:02,277 --> 00:31:03,611
[agent 3] Hands behind your head.

365
00:31:04,821 --> 00:31:07,240
-[Melvin] Please! I gotta get to her!
-[agent 3] On your knees.

366
00:31:07,323 --> 00:31:08,324
On your knees!

367
00:31:12,912 --> 00:31:14,163
[Melvin] Betsy!

368
00:31:14,956 --> 00:31:17,041
He'll hurt Betsy!

369
00:31:22,755 --> 00:31:25,466
-He asleep?
-Been in bed all night.

370
00:31:26,509 --> 00:31:27,594
[Ray] I need to talk to him.

371
00:31:27,677 --> 00:31:31,097
-You want company?
-No. I got it.

372
00:31:36,519 --> 00:31:38,187
[Manning] Potter's in custody.

373
00:31:38,271 --> 00:31:41,608
Should we alter his situation
or his girlfriend's?

374
00:31:41,691 --> 00:31:42,692
No.

375
00:31:44,569 --> 00:31:46,362
He's irrelevant now.

376
00:31:50,158 --> 00:31:51,576
Where is Poindexter?

377
00:31:51,659 --> 00:31:53,119
Laying low, as ordered.

378
00:31:53,828 --> 00:31:56,414
Although, I'm concerned
about his mental stability.

379
00:31:56,497 --> 00:31:57,498
Yeah.

380
00:31:59,584 --> 00:32:01,920
I've demanded a lot from him.

381
00:32:02,003 --> 00:32:03,546
You keep an eye on him.

382
00:32:05,924 --> 00:32:07,759
But let him be for now.

383
00:32:53,638 --> 00:32:54,973
We need to talk.

384
00:32:56,265 --> 00:32:58,059
You're working late.

385
00:32:58,142 --> 00:33:01,729
Shouldn't you be with your family?
Seema, isn't it?

386
00:33:01,813 --> 00:33:03,898
Say her name again and see what happens.

387
00:33:09,904 --> 00:33:11,864
What can I help you with?

388
00:33:11,948 --> 00:33:14,409
[scoffs] Help me.

389
00:33:16,327 --> 00:33:19,497
You know, you remind me of someone
I knew growing up.

390
00:33:20,081 --> 00:33:21,249
Jack Kem.

391
00:33:22,667 --> 00:33:25,503
Yeah, but everyone knew him as Jiggy.

392
00:33:25,586 --> 00:33:29,424
You know, Jiggy lived
in a two-family house all by himself.

393
00:33:30,341 --> 00:33:32,468
It was practically a mansion to me.

394
00:33:33,219 --> 00:33:34,846
But Jiggy was a helper, too.

395
00:33:35,430 --> 00:33:38,349
He was always
helping out folks on the block.

396
00:33:39,058 --> 00:33:43,563
Annie the single mom needs a new car.
Jiggy's got it.

397
00:33:43,646 --> 00:33:47,608
The Hoffmans are desperate for rent.
No problem.

398
00:33:49,610 --> 00:33:52,155
Ten-year-old me
thought this guy was a hero.

399
00:33:55,450 --> 00:33:58,327
But it turned out
Jiggy had hidden ten kilos of heroin

400
00:33:58,411 --> 00:33:59,996
in the trunk of Annie's sedan.

401
00:34:00,997 --> 00:34:03,499
Another five in the Hoffman baby's room.

402
00:34:06,419 --> 00:34:09,297
Guess who the cops arrested
when they tracked down that powder?

403
00:34:12,133 --> 00:34:13,009
[Ray scoffs]

404
00:34:13,885 --> 00:34:16,095
I've seen your kind of help before.

405
00:34:22,185 --> 00:34:26,064
Have a little faith in me,
Special Agent Nadeem.

406
00:34:27,982 --> 00:34:30,693
I'm a better man than Jiggy.

407
00:34:31,986 --> 00:34:33,112
This...

408
00:34:34,822 --> 00:34:36,324
All of this...

409
00:34:40,119 --> 00:34:42,497
This was my price,

410
00:34:43,247 --> 00:34:46,793
which I was plain about
at the start of our relationship.

411
00:34:48,127 --> 00:34:50,046
And you have paid it.

412
00:34:54,759 --> 00:34:56,219
I need to know.

413
00:34:57,595 --> 00:34:58,763
Right now.

414
00:35:01,682 --> 00:35:06,145
You let Jasper Evans out of prison
to pay him back for shanking you?

415
00:35:08,856 --> 00:35:12,610
Your desperation diminishes you,
Special Agent.

416
00:35:14,028 --> 00:35:15,279
Good night.

417
00:36:09,208 --> 00:36:13,171
[Fisk] "The Hero of Hell's Kitchen
Feeds a Simpleton to the Feds."

418
00:36:14,088 --> 00:36:17,091
Won't that make a hell of a headline
for tomorrow's <i>Bulletin?</i>

419
00:36:18,342 --> 00:36:19,844
Melvin made his choice.

420
00:36:21,137 --> 00:36:24,015
Yet you did hesitate before you left. Were you waiting for a messenger
from the Lord to stop you,

421
00:36:27,727 --> 00:36:30,354
like he stopped Abraham
from killing his son?

422
00:36:31,272 --> 00:36:34,066
Were you disappointed
no messenger arrived...

423
00:36:34,150 --> 00:36:40,156
or relieved that you didn't have to risk
your life for a weak-minded criminal?

424
00:36:50,082 --> 00:36:53,502
You're not strong enough
to beat the man I sent for you.

425
00:36:53,586 --> 00:36:55,796
You're not smart enough to beat me.

426
00:36:55,880 --> 00:36:59,133
You couldn't do it alone.
You couldn't do it with your friends.

427
00:37:00,343 --> 00:37:03,012
Your father never knew when to lay down.

428
00:37:04,222 --> 00:37:05,806
He was too proud.

429
00:37:06,349 --> 00:37:08,100
You will die the same way.

430
00:37:29,163 --> 00:37:31,374
Please, Betsy, don't do me like this.

431
00:37:31,457 --> 00:37:34,585
I wasn't the one who violated parole.
You did this to yourself.

432
00:37:37,421 --> 00:37:38,881
-[Matt] Betsy.
-[gasps]

433
00:37:38,965 --> 00:37:43,719
Don't. I'm not here to hurt you.
I'm here about Melvin.

434
00:37:46,138 --> 00:37:48,099
Melvin Potter?

435
00:37:48,182 --> 00:37:49,809
[Matt] He's been arrested.

436
00:37:49,892 --> 00:37:50,893
Bullshit.

437
00:37:50,977 --> 00:37:53,020
He's not gonna tell anyone
about your relationship,

438
00:37:53,104 --> 00:37:54,939
but that's not
what you need to worry about.

439
00:37:55,856 --> 00:37:57,400
You need to worry about Wilson Fisk.

440
00:37:57,483 --> 00:38:00,236
Oh, shit. Damn it, Melvin.

441
00:38:00,319 --> 00:38:03,114
Fisk doesn't leave loose ends.
He will kill you.

442
00:38:03,197 --> 00:38:07,785
Don't go home. Don't go back to work.
Leave town.

443
00:38:07,868 --> 00:38:09,578
[Betsy] What about Melvin? Is he okay?

444
00:38:09,662 --> 00:38:11,038
You can't help Melvin.

445
00:38:11,122 --> 00:38:13,624
He made his bed
when he went back to work for Fisk.

446
00:38:16,335 --> 00:38:18,504
You're a cold piece of work, aren't you?

447
00:38:19,297 --> 00:38:21,716
Melvin told me
about the Devil of Hell's Kitchen.

448
00:38:21,799 --> 00:38:23,718
He thought you were a hero.

449
00:38:24,635 --> 00:38:27,972
I told him assholes like you and Fisk
are cut from the same cloth

450
00:38:28,055 --> 00:38:30,308
and both of you
would take advantage of Melvin

451
00:38:30,391 --> 00:38:32,977
because he has a good heart
and a trusting way!

452
00:38:33,060 --> 00:38:34,562
You've been warned, Betsy.

453
00:38:34,937 --> 00:38:36,605
You want to live?

454
00:38:36,689 --> 00:38:37,690
Run. [Marci] Foggy?

455
00:38:59,045 --> 00:39:00,755
Foggy, baby, are you okay?

456
00:39:01,547 --> 00:39:03,424
Because I don't think you're okay.

457
00:39:03,966 --> 00:39:04,800
Oh.

458
00:39:05,593 --> 00:39:06,969
I'm-- I'm fine.

459
00:39:10,222 --> 00:39:12,183
I think I know what Fisk is up to.

460
00:39:17,855 --> 00:39:19,315
[crying and sniffling]

461
00:39:59,855 --> 00:40:00,940
[line ringing]

462
00:40:06,112 --> 00:40:07,154
[man] <i>Hello?</i>

463
00:40:09,865 --> 00:40:14,245
-Hi, Dad. It's me.
-<i>Karen? Good Lord.</i>

464
00:40:14,912 --> 00:40:19,333
<i>I heard something on the news.</i>
<i>That wasn't where you work, was it?</i>

465
00:40:19,417 --> 00:40:22,420
Yeah. Yeah, it was. I'm okay, though.

466
00:40:25,047 --> 00:40:29,969
I was thinking that maybe
I could come home for a little while.

467
00:40:33,681 --> 00:40:36,434
<i>I don't know.</i>
<i>I'm afraid the timing is not great.</i>

468
00:40:40,312 --> 00:40:42,565
Yeah. Of course. I get it.

469
00:40:43,107 --> 00:40:45,151
<i>But you can call anytime, all right?</i>

470
00:40:51,949 --> 00:40:52,992
Dad...

471
00:40:53,993 --> 00:40:57,246
I was just trying to do the right thing.
It just...

472
00:40:58,038 --> 00:40:59,373
It went all wrong.

473
00:41:02,710 --> 00:41:04,378
<i>That's what you do, Karen.</i>

474
00:41:06,922 --> 00:41:08,090
<i>Good night.</i>

475
00:41:11,093 --> 00:41:12,386
[sobbing]

476
00:41:30,863 --> 00:41:32,781
[Ray] I'm not asking for prisoner files.

477
00:41:32,865 --> 00:41:36,118
All I want is footage
from the security cameras. Copies.

478
00:41:37,244 --> 00:41:38,412
I'll even pay for them.

479
00:41:41,081 --> 00:41:43,542
We're supposed to be
on the same side here.

480
00:41:43,626 --> 00:41:47,004
All I want to do is see exactly
what happened when Fisk got shanked.

481
00:41:49,590 --> 00:41:52,843
Well, you have him call me
as soon as he gets in. Understand?

482
00:41:53,511 --> 00:41:54,345
I'll--

483
00:41:55,721 --> 00:41:56,764
Asshole.

484
00:42:13,822 --> 00:42:15,783
[all] Surprise!

485
00:42:15,866 --> 00:42:16,867
[Seema laughing]

486
00:42:16,951 --> 00:42:18,410
Wow. [chuckles]

487
00:42:19,245 --> 00:42:21,497
[Seema] Congratulations
on your promotion, <i>nuuri.</i>

488
00:42:21,580 --> 00:42:22,581
Thanks, everyone.

489
00:42:22,665 --> 00:42:24,875
Hey, bud. Come here.

490
00:42:29,421 --> 00:42:30,839
Sorry I'm late.

491
00:42:35,386 --> 00:42:37,012
[clinking glass]

492
00:42:37,429 --> 00:42:42,935
Ray, you make every single person
in this room so proud.

493
00:42:43,602 --> 00:42:47,022
Proud of the man you are
and who you strive to be.

494
00:42:47,106 --> 00:42:49,358
For the example you set for our son.

495
00:42:50,234 --> 00:42:52,987
For the husband and friend we adore.

496
00:42:53,070 --> 00:42:55,698
And for being the man
who hogs more blankets at night

497
00:42:55,781 --> 00:42:58,325
-than is humanly possible.
-[all chuckle]

498
00:42:59,159 --> 00:43:03,914
But even with that, you've always been
the person to warm my heart.

499
00:43:05,332 --> 00:43:08,669
Congratulations
on your well-deserved promotion.

500
00:43:08,752 --> 00:43:10,254
-[man] Cheers.
-[woman] Congratulations.

501
00:43:10,337 --> 00:43:12,298
-I love you.
-I love you.

502
00:43:12,381 --> 00:43:13,382
Eww.

503
00:43:14,925 --> 00:43:16,427
Way to kill the moment, buddy.

504
00:43:16,510 --> 00:43:19,555
-[chuckles]
-Mom, we're out of soda.

505
00:43:19,638 --> 00:43:21,932
[Seema] There's plenty
in the fridge downstairs.

506
00:43:22,016 --> 00:43:23,058
I'll get it.

507
00:43:23,642 --> 00:43:25,227
I need a moment with you first.

508
00:43:29,732 --> 00:43:30,733
What?

509
00:43:34,028 --> 00:43:36,739
-I told you, everything is fine.
-You lied to me.

510
00:43:37,448 --> 00:43:40,534
I called you, afraid for your life,
and you lied.

511
00:43:40,618 --> 00:43:43,787
I have to hear from Annie Wellers
what really happened?

512
00:43:43,871 --> 00:43:46,957
That that murderer attacked you
and that you shot him?

513
00:43:47,041 --> 00:43:48,876
-Seems--
-I have to hear it from her?

514
00:43:51,086 --> 00:43:53,839
-I didn't want you to worry.
-Well, I am worried.

515
00:43:53,922 --> 00:43:57,718
I'm worried what this job
is doing to you, to us.

516
00:43:59,094 --> 00:44:00,304
What's that supposed to mean?

517
00:44:00,387 --> 00:44:03,265
I will always have your back.
To them. To everyone.

518
00:44:04,600 --> 00:44:06,393
But I'm not an idiot.

519
00:44:07,269 --> 00:44:10,314
-I didn't say you are.
-When you lie to my face, you do.

520
00:44:19,615 --> 00:44:20,699
You're right.

521
00:44:23,661 --> 00:44:26,121
I'm just trying
to keep everything together.

522
00:44:27,873 --> 00:44:30,542
I don't want to screw any of this up.

523
00:44:31,794 --> 00:44:35,714
I worked so hard for this, for us.

524
00:44:39,802 --> 00:44:41,679
How-- How can I fix this?

525
00:44:46,892 --> 00:44:48,852
You can start with telling me the truth.

526
00:44:52,064 --> 00:44:54,108
And by getting more drinks.

527
00:44:56,110 --> 00:44:57,277
[chuckles]

528
00:45:09,832 --> 00:45:10,916
[sighs]

529
00:45:29,893 --> 00:45:32,563
-[Ray grunting]
-I didn't come here to fight.

530
00:45:36,775 --> 00:45:38,277
[panting]

531
00:45:41,613 --> 00:45:42,865
Who are you?

532
00:45:44,408 --> 00:45:45,617
I'm Daredevil.

533
00:45:46,535 --> 00:45:47,703
The real one.

534
00:46:05,429 --> 00:46:07,848
-You don't look like--
-I buried the red suit.

535
00:46:08,932 --> 00:46:11,727
The man who attacked the <i>Bulletin,</i>
he resurrected it.

536
00:46:14,563 --> 00:46:18,650
You do, however, match the description
of a guy who's been tuning up FBI agents.

537
00:46:18,734 --> 00:46:23,155
Which is the last thing I ever wanted,
but you people haven't left me any choice.

538
00:46:24,656 --> 00:46:28,410
If you'd just wake the hell up instead
of playing right into Fisk's hands.

539
00:46:28,494 --> 00:46:32,164
He's using you, and I think you know it.

540
00:46:33,582 --> 00:46:35,959
Now, I heard you confront
that psycho at the <i>Bulletin.</i>

541
00:46:36,043 --> 00:46:39,004
I heard you try to stop him,
and he almost killed you, too.

542
00:46:39,087 --> 00:46:41,298
So let me ask you this, Agent Nadeem...

543
00:46:42,841 --> 00:46:44,676
Who do you think is the danger here?

544
00:46:45,427 --> 00:46:46,428
Me... or him?

545
00:46:50,265 --> 00:46:51,892
-[shushes]
-[door opens]

546
00:46:52,476 --> 00:46:55,020
[Sami] Dad, Mom wants to know
where you are.

547
00:46:56,563 --> 00:46:58,065
Don't come down, Sami.

548
00:46:59,107 --> 00:47:01,360
I dropped a beer, there's glass.

549
00:47:03,987 --> 00:47:07,074
Tell your mom I need
a couple of minutes to clean it up.

550
00:47:07,157 --> 00:47:08,158
[Sami] Okay.

551
00:47:08,742 --> 00:47:09,660
[door closes]

552
00:47:12,120 --> 00:47:15,833
Let's say I believe the guy
that just broke into my house.

553
00:47:16,959 --> 00:47:18,293
Let's just say that.

554
00:47:20,587 --> 00:47:21,797
What do you got?

555
00:47:23,340 --> 00:47:26,426
The man who attacked the <i>Bulletin</i>
dressed as Daredevil...

556
00:47:28,095 --> 00:47:29,555
he's in the FBI.

557
00:47:38,230 --> 00:47:39,481
Keep talking.

